main event: Two unidentified radar contacts were observed on 8 June 1960, indicating large objects with a length of 2-5 miles.
interesting points: The radar detected two significant bursts lasting 1-2 minutes each., The objects were reported at a distance of about 3-5 miles., Contacts were confirmed not to be weather phenomena such as clouds., Multiple military branches were informed about the sightings., The conclusions included possibilities of being a balloon, aircraft, or astronomical phenomena.
